 Zwickau [->span<-] News [->span<-] Newsletter [->span<-] Hilfe & Kontakt [->span<-] Karriere [->span<-] H\u00e4ndlersuche [->span<-] Gesch\u00e4ftskunden [->span<-] Information zur Barrierefreiheit [->span<-] Ersthelfer/ first responder [->span<-] Volkswagen Konzern [->span<-] Investor Relations [->span<-] Compliance [->span<-] Kontakt Cyber Security [->span<-] Volkswagen Nutzfahrzeuge [->span<-] Facebook [->span<-] Instagram [->span<-] YouTube [->span<-] TikTok [->span<-] LinkedIn [->span<-] Impressum [->span<-] Nutzungsbedingungen [->span<-] Datenschutzerkl\u00e4rungen [->span<-] Cookie-Richtlinie [->span<-] Lizenzhinweise Dritter [->span<-] Angaben zum Digital Services Act (DSA) [->span<-] EU Data Act [->span<-] Produktsicherheitsinformationen [->span<-] VERTRAG WIDERRUFEN [->span<-] Zubeh\u00f6r [->span<-] z.\u00a0B."]], ["b", ["[->b<-] Werkbesichtigung [->b<-]  hinter die Kulissen [->b<-] \u00a0Werk Wolfsburg [->b<-] Vom Traditionsunternehmen zum Werk der Superlative [->b<-] Standortbesichtigung [->b<-] Werk Braunschweig [->b<-] Anschrift [->b<-] Kontakt [->b<-]  Werk Emden [->b<-] Bitte beachten Sie: [->b<-] Anschrift [->b<-] Kontakt [->b<-]   [->b<-] Email [->b<-] Werk Hannover [->b<-] Anmeldung [->b<-] Reservierung [->b<-] Anschrift [->b<-] Kontakt [->b<-]  Werk Kassel [->b<-] Anmeldung [->b<-] Bitte beachten Sie: [->b<-] Reservierung: [->b<-] Anschrift und Kontakt [->b<-] Anschrift [->b<-] Kontakt [->b<-]  Werk Salzgitter [->b<-] Das Werk [->b<-] Derzeit werden keine Werktouren im Werk Salzgitter angeboten.\u00a0 [->b<-] Anschrift [->b<-] Kontakt [->b<-]  Datenschutzerkl\u00e4rung [->b<-] Motorenwerk Chemnitz. [->b<-] Die Gl\u00e4serne Manufaktur Dresden. [->b<-] Fahrzeugwerk Zwickau. [->b<-] Motorenwerk Chemnitz. [->b<-] Die Gl\u00e4serne Manufaktur Dresden. [->b<-] Fahrzeugwerk Zwickau."]], ["em", ["[->em<-] "]]], [["p", ["[->p<-] Come on in! We are opening up our factory halls to you. On our tailor-made tours through the different vehicle production areas, we show you how a [->p<-]   [->p<-]  is made. Discover the fascinating variety in the production at our sites with our experts and experience up-close what makes a [->p<-]   [->p<-]  unique. We look forward to showing you around! [->p<-] Come with us as we delve into the fascinating world of vehicle production and experience the perfect symbiosis of the traditional and the modern at the main factory in Wolfsburg.\u00a0 [->p<-] Ever since the legendary Beetle first rolled off the production line in 1945, this factory has gone from strength to strength. Spanning more than 6.5 km\u00b2, the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  factory in Wolfsburg is now the largest automotive plant in Europe, employing more than 60,000 people.  [->p<-] Approx. 200,000 visitors a year come to Wolfsburg to experience the production process. On our tailor-made factory tours through the different production areas, we give you an exclusive, close-up insight into how a [->p<-]   [->p<-]  is made. [->p<-]   [->p<-]  it live. [->p<-] At our oldest site, everything revolves around axles, steering units, battery systems, tool making and mechanical engineering. [->p<-] Brunswick (Braunschweig) is where the very first [->p<-]   [->p<-]  AG factory was established. Today it is synonymous with advanced technical expertise in innovative battery systems and state-of-the-art electromechanical steering systems. The site is one of the biggest world-leading producers of chassis components. Production and development take place under one roof. [->p<-] The Braunschweig factory is the oldest [->p<-]   [->p<-]  factory of them all. It is now part of the Components Group within the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  Group and the lead plant for the areas of chassis and battery systems. With its three plants, the site is now synonymous with advanced technical expertise and is one of the world\u2019s premier chassis component factories. Some 7,000 people work here. Many products are made in Braunschweig: axles, steering systems, brake pads, pivot bearings, shock absorbers and, of course, battery systems. For the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  alone, the majority of chassis components originate from Braunschweig. Moreover, entire production systems are built in the tooling unit. On the tour, visitors experience a combination of tradition and modernity and a classic production facility.\u00a0 [->p<-] Visits can be held by arrangement on all production days from Monday to Friday at 10:00 a.m. and 2:00 p.m. The visit lasts around two hours. The maximum group size is 30 people. Please book well in advance if you wish to visit the Brunswick factory with a group. Children under the age of 10 are unfortunately not able to take part in a factory visit. [->p<-] As all tours involve walking though production areas, sturdy shoes are compulsory. [->p<-] Photography and filming is prohibited on the entire factory site. Camera phones and audio recordings are also prohibited. [->p<-] We reserve the right to make changes to the itinerary and to cancel the FactoryTour for operational reasons at short notice. We do not accept any liability for any loss incurred as a result of this. [->p<-]  AG [->p<-] Besucherdienste\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] Postfach 3976 [->p<-] 38037 Braunschweig [->p<-] Visitor services at the Braunschweig factory [->p<-] Visit the car factory by the sea. [->p<-] The [->p<-]   [->p<-]  plant in Emden was founded in 1964. The first Beetle rolled off the production line the same year. Many other models followed. [->p<-]   [->p<-]  in Emden is the largest employer west of Bremen and north of Ruhr area. To date, a total of over 12 million vehicles have been produced here. The plant has a total area of around 4,3 million square meters. The site also includes parking spaces for shipping vehicles and a driving test track. [->p<-] Since 2020, the factory has been converted for the production of electric vehicles while it was still in operation. Today, the fully electric models [->p<-]   [->p<-] , ID.7 and the ID. 7 Tourer are manufactured at the Emden plant. On our factory tour through production, specially designed for visitor groups, you can experience vehicle production up close. [->p<-] Our visitor tour includes a digital site presentation as well as a tour of the press shop, body shop, and loading station with a view of the harbor. [->p<-] The assembly hall is not open to visitors until autumn 2026. [->p<-] Tours take place by appointment Monday to Friday at 9:30 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. No tours are offered on weekends, non-production days or during factory holidays. Tours can be booked by groups or individuals. For organisational reasons, the maximum size of a visitor group is limited to 30 people. Children aged 6 and above are welcome to take part in the tour.\u00a0\u00a0 [->p<-] The factory tours are conducted in German. [->p<-] The assembly hall is temporarily closed to visitors. [->p<-] The replacement tours include a digital presentation of the site and a tour of the press shop, body shop and loading station. [->p<-] Photography and filming are prohibited throughout the factory premises, and camera phones and audio recordings are also not permitted. We reserve the right to make short-term changes to the schedule and to cancel the factory tour for operational reasons. We cannot accept any liability for any damage incurred as a result. [->p<-] \u00a0AG Werk Emden [->p<-] Besucherdienste [->p<-] Niedersachsenstra\u00dfe [->p<-] 26723 Emden [->p<-] Besucherdienst Werk Emden [->p<-] Tel.: +49 (0) 4921-86-2390 [->p<-] If you arrive by bus, please note that you must report to the entrance gate with your registration confirmation. All visitors must get off in front of the main gate and register individually with their valid ID card or passport. Please note that the registration process can take 3-4 minutes per visitor. Please therefore plan enough time before the start of the tour. Thank you for your understanding. [->p<-] Visit our Hanover factory on a virtual tour with live audio commentary. This is where the popular T series and the fully electric ID. Buzz are built. [->p<-]   [->p<-]  the fascinating world of automotive production from the comfort of your screen at home. [->p<-] Production of the \u2018Bulli\u2019 microbus at the Hanover-St\u00f6cken plant got under way on 8 March 1956. Here, some 9.23 million T series vehicles have been built to date. Explore the diversity of our products and their production stages, from the pressing plant (photo) and paint works through to vehicle assembly. [->p<-] With some 13,500 employees, the commercial vehicle factory in St\u00f6cken is the largest industrial employer in the Hanover region and, with almost 600 apprentices and students on an industry placement, is also the largest industrial apprentice provider. The factory spans some 1.1 million square metres, which equates to the size of approximately 152 football pitches. [->p<-] Digital tours take place individually in Hanover by appointment. No tours are offered on weekends or public holidays. [->p<-] The tours are conducted in German and, if required, in English, and last approximately 60 minutes. [->p<-] To book a digital tour, please send us an email at: [->p<-]  Nutzfahrzeuge [->p<-] Mecklenheidestra\u00dfe 74 [->p<-] 30419 Hannover [->p<-] Ms. Janina Danielzik [->p<-] Tel. +49 (0)511 798 2139 [->p<-] The [->p<-]   [->p<-]  factory in the Baunatal district of Kassel has been making transmissions and chassis parts for many Group brands. What\u2019s more, the Kassel factory boasts the largest and most advanced logistics centre in Europe. [->p<-] Explore many different areas of the second-largest [->p<-]   [->p<-]  factory in Germany and watch as more than 16,500 manufacturing employees work on various transmissions and myriad chassis parts. [->p<-] Viewings are available by appointment on production days from Monday to Friday at 10:30 am. The duration is about two hours. [->p<-] A tour takes place with a minimum of 8 and a maximum of 25 people. [->p<-] Individuals or larger groups can be planned individually. [->p<-] Children under the age of 10 cannot join a tour. [->p<-] The tours are covered on foot through the production areas, so sturdy shoes are mandatory. [->p<-] Photography and filming are prohibited on the entire factory premises, and camera phones or audio recordings are also not permitted. We reserve the right to make short-term changes to the schedule as well as to cancel the factory tour for operational reasons. We cannot assume any liability for any damage caused by this. [->p<-] To request a factory tour, please send the completed form to  [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-]  AG Kassel [->p<-] Besucherdienste [->p<-] Dr. Rudolf-Leiding-Platz 1 [->p<-] Postfach 4976 [->p<-] 34225 Baunatal [->p<-] Kassel factory, Visitor Services [->p<-] Tel.: +49 (0) 561 490 2099\u00a0 [->p<-] \u00a0 [->p<-] The Salzgitter factory produces engines and engine parts for the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  Group brands. [->p<-] Change and transformation \u2013 this is already a tradition in Salzgitter. Built in 1970 as a vehicle plant for the K70, the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  components site in Salzgitter today manufactures engine variants for over 40 models in the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  Group as well as important e-components that are used in the vehicle models of [->p<-]   [->p<-] 's ID. family. [->p<-] In the future, the Salzgitter site is to become the battery center for the [->p<-]   [->p<-]  Group. The transition to future technologies is already in full swing. [->p<-]  Group Components [->p<-]  Aktiengesellschaft [->p<-] Brieffach 7972 [->p<-] Industriestra\u00dfe Nord [->p<-] 38231 Salzgitter [->p<-] Besucherdienst Salzgitter [->p<-] Read our "]], ["div", ["[->div<-] \u00a9 Volkswagen 2026 [->div<-] Die in dieser Darstellung gezeigten Fahrzeuge und Ausstattungen k\u00f6nnen in einzelnen Details vom aktuellen deutschen Lieferprogramm abweichen. Abgebildet sind teilweise Sonderausstattungen der Fahrzeuge gegen Mehrpreis. [->div<-] \r\nBitte be